      height="595"
      loading="lazy"
    />
    <figcaption>Alfa Laval NX-314 Decanter Centrifuge for Sunflower Oil</figcaption>
  </figure>
  <p>
    A mechanical expeller crushes sunflower and other similar oil seeds to extract the oil contained in the seeds. The oil from the expeller carries seed debris and other contaminant particles. The process must remove this sediment contaminant before the producer can use the oil.
  </p>
  <p>
    An Alfa Laval decanter centrifuge can separate the seed debris and other sediments, such as dirt and sand, from the oil.
  </p>
  <p>
    The photograph above shows a complete sunflower oil separating decanter centrifuge module designed and <a href="/about-dolphin-centrifuge/">manufactured by Dolphin Centrifuge</a>. The module includes an Alfa Laval NX-314 decanter with feed and transfer pumps and a clean oil tank with all auxiliary sensors and instruments.
  </p>

  <!-- THC (Cannabis Extraction) -->
  <h3 id="thc-cannabis">THC (Cannabis Extraction)</h3>
  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
    <figure>
      <img
        src="/images/decanter-centrifuge-applications/Alfa-Laval-Class-1-Div-2-THC-Cannabis-Decanter-800.webp"
